# n8n Node Development

- Prefer declarative nodes for REST APIs; use programmatic `execute()` only for triggers, GraphQL, complex transforms, external integrations, or full versioning needs.
- The node class name must match the node filename: `Omnifact` in `Omnifact.node.ts`.
- Use n8n helpers for HTTP: `this.helpers.httpRequest()` or `this.helpers.httpRequestWithAuthentication()`. Do not use `axios`, `fetch`, or `got`.
- Never mutate input data; clone before changing values.
- Always preserve item pairing with `constructExecutionMetaData` or `pairedItem`.
- For programmatic operations, wrap errors with `NodeOperationError(this.getNode(), error, { itemIndex })` and respect `continueOnFail()`.
- Reuse field `value` strings across operations when possible so user-entered data persists while switching operations.
- Import runtime values separately from types.

## UI Parameters

- Use Title Case for `displayName` and option `name`.
- Use sentence case for `description`, `action`, and `hint`.
- Boolean descriptions must start with `Whether...`.
- Placeholders must start with `e.g. ...`.
- Operation `action` text must include the resource name.
- Field order should be Resource, Operation, required fields, then `Additional Fields`.
- `resource` and `operation` parameters require `noDataExpression: true`.
- Optional fields belong in an `Additional Fields` collection with `placeholder: 'Add Field'`.
- Use `resourceLocator` for selecting one external item.
- Add a simplify parameter when responses contain more than 10 fields.
- Delete operations should return `[{ deleted: true }]`.
